race.comment: The free-rolling SUNSET PARK (6) continued her good form this prep when a close fourth over 1900m at Canterbury after leading. Gave a sight but found one better in a similar race to this two starts back. Runs very well for Alysha Collett and the combination will be hard to peg back again. OTONO (11) has settled back in the field and struggled to make inroads in a couple of Highways over shorter trips since resuming. Lightly raced mare who needs 1800m now. Jay Ford back on is worth noting as he is two-for-two on the five-year-old. HARLOW MIST (1) did nothing first-up in a BM78 over 1500m at Rosehill. Won't find this as tough and the extra trip suits. Capable of sharp improvement. THINK WE'RE THERE (10) went back from a wide draw and was never in the hunt at Newcastle last time. Drops 7.5kgs with the claim and strips fitter at the third run back. IRISH BLISS (13) can fill a top-four spot with the light weight.
